The most important are Lazarus' touching words, the only ones of their kind, where the state calls not just immigrants but "the poorest of the poor": "Your tired, your Poor, / Your huddled masses yearning to break free, / The written relief of your theme store."
The poem is now more topical than ever.
Miller did not practice literature criticism, he made it clear that the "poorest" are not welcome in Trump's United States.
