Ferrell followed a real-time video of police standing in front of protesters with a barking dog.
He also said he saw a video of another cop arming his rifle and shouting, "I'm going to kill all of you... animals."
"This isn't normal," Ferrell remembers saying.
"It wasn't the kind of murder we've already gotten used to and could be called typical.
That's when I felt the chills.
I was angry and I cried.
He booked a return flight home for the next day.
The plane landed at 11 o'clock in the evening and Ferrell picked up his six-year-old daughter from his father's house and decided they would leave for Ferguson the next morning.
About what happened to Ferrell and Ferguson over the next three years, a documentary entitled "Whose Streets?" was made, premiered in cinemas on August 11, 2017.
